    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-02-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-03-02T15:43:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Physician Assistants Continuity of Care Act of 2007 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to permit a physician assistant, when delegated by a physician, to: (1) certify that inpatient psychiatric hospital services or post-hospital extended care services are required; (2) establish and review a plan for home health services; and (3) certify a terminal illness with respect to hospice care.</p><p>Covers as hospice care any legally authorized services of a physician assistant performed under a physician's supervision.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
